#. HTML: </p><h3>
msgctxt "dn9:38.23"
msgid "2.2. Tayoattapaṭilābha "
msgstr "2.2. Three Kinds of Reincarnation "

# NOTE: Comm: Tattha attapaṭilābhoti attabhāvapaṭilābho, ettha ca bhagavā tīhi attabhāvapaṭilābhehi tayo bhave dassesi
#. HTML: </h3><p>
#. REF: pts-cs39, sc61
msgctxt "dn9:39.1"
msgid "“Tayo kho me, poṭṭhapāda, attapaṭilābhā—"
msgstr "“Poṭṭhapāda, there are these three kinds of reincarnation: "

msgctxt "dn9:39.2"
msgid "oḷāriko attapaṭilābho, manomayo attapaṭilābho, arūpo attapaṭilābho. "
msgstr "a substantial reincarnation, a mind-made reincarnation, and a non-physical reincarnation. "

msgctxt "dn9:39.3"
msgid "Katamo ca, poṭṭhapāda, oḷāriko attapaṭilābho? "
msgstr "And what is a substantial reincarnation? "

msgctxt "dn9:39.4"
msgid "Rūpī cātumahābhūtiko kabaḷīkārāhārabhakkho, ayaṃ oḷāriko attapaṭilābho. "
msgstr "It is physical, made up of the four primary elements, and consumes solid food. "

msgctxt "dn9:39.5"
msgid "Katamo manomayo attapaṭilābho? "
msgstr "What is a mind-made reincarnation? "

msgctxt "dn9:39.6"
msgid "Rūpī manomayo sabbaṅgapaccaṅgī ahīnindriyo, ayaṃ manomayo attapaṭilābho. "
msgstr "It is physical, mind-made, complete in all its various parts, not deficient in any faculty. "

msgctxt "dn9:39.7"
msgid "Katamo arūpo attapaṭilābho? "
msgstr "What is a non-physical reincarnation? "

msgctxt "dn9:39.8"
msgid "Arūpī saññāmayo, ayaṃ arūpo attapaṭilābho. "
msgstr "It is non-physical, made of perception. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts-cs40, pts-vp-pli1.196, sc62
msgctxt "dn9:40.1"
msgid "Oḷārikassapi kho ahaṃ, poṭṭhapāda, attapaṭilābhassa pahānāya dhammaṃ desemi: "
msgstr "I teach the Dhamma for the giving up of these three kinds of reincarnation: "

msgctxt "dn9:40.2"
msgid "‘yathāpaṭipannānaṃ vo saṅkilesikā dhammā pahīyissanti, vodāniyā dhammā abhivaḍḍhissanti, paññāpāripūriṃ vepullattañca diṭṭheva dhamme sayaṃ abhiññā sacchikatvā upasampajja viharissathā’ti. "
msgstr "‘When you practice accordingly, corrupting qualities will be given up in you and cleansing qualities will grow. You’ll enter and remain in the fullness and abundance of wisdom, having realized it with your own insight in this very life.’ "

msgctxt "dn9:40.3"
msgid "Siyā kho pana te, poṭṭhapāda, evamassa: "
msgstr "Poṭṭhapāda, you might think: "

# NOTE: I find the syntax of this passage perplexing. Compare the similar sentiment at SN 22.2, which has a much more clear syntax.
msgctxt "dn9:40.4"
msgid "‘saṅkilesikā dhammā pahīyissanti, vodāniyā dhammā abhivaḍḍhissanti, paññāpāripūriṃ vepullattañca diṭṭheva dhamme sayaṃ abhiññā sacchikatvā upasampajja viharissati, dukkho ca kho vihāro’ti. "
msgstr "‘Corrupting qualities will be given up and cleansing qualities will grow. One will enter and remain in the fullness and abundance of wisdom, having realized it with one’s own insight in this very life. But such a life is suffering.’ "

msgctxt "dn9:40.5"
msgid "Na kho panetaṃ, poṭṭhapāda, evaṃ daṭṭhabbaṃ. "
msgstr "But you should not see it like this. "

msgctxt "dn9:40.6"
msgid "Saṅkilesikā ceva dhammā pahīyissanti, vodāniyā ca dhammā abhivaḍḍhissanti, paññāpāripūriṃ vepullattañca diṭṭheva dhamme sayaṃ abhiññā sacchikatvā upasampajja viharissati, pāmujjañceva bhavissati pīti ca passaddhi ca sati ca sampajaññañca sukho ca vihāro. "
msgstr "Corrupting qualities will be given up and cleansing qualities will grow. One will enter and remain in the fullness and abundance of wisdom, having realized it with one’s own insight in this very life. And there will be only joy and happiness, tranquility, mindfulness and awareness. Such a life is blissful. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts-cs41, sc63
