msgstr "‘But reverends, what is that mind-made reincarnation?’ We’d answer like this, "

msgctxt "dn9:44.3"
msgid "Tesaṃ mayaṃ evaṃ puṭṭhā evaṃ byākareyyāma: "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "dn9:44.4"
msgid "‘ayaṃ vā so, āvuso, manomayo attapaṭilābho yassa mayaṃ pahānāya dhammaṃ desema, yathāpaṭipannānaṃ vo saṅkilesikā dhammā pahīyissanti, vodāniyā dhammā abhivaḍḍhissanti, paññāpāripūriṃ vepullattañca diṭṭheva dhamme sayaṃ abhiññā sacchikatvā upasampajja viharissathā’ti. "
msgstr "‘This is that mind-made reincarnation.’ "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts-cs45, sc67
msgctxt "dn9:45.1"
msgid "Pare ce, poṭṭhapāda, amhe evaṃ puccheyyuṃ: "
msgstr "If others should ask us, "

msgctxt "dn9:45.2"
msgid "‘katamo pana so, āvuso, arūpo attapaṭilābho, yassa tumhe pahānāya dhammaṃ desetha, yathāpaṭipannānaṃ vo saṅkilesikā dhammā pahīyissanti, vodāniyā dhammā abhivaḍḍhissanti, paññāpāripūriṃ vepullattañca diṭṭheva dhamme sayaṃ abhiññā sacchikatvā upasampajja viharissathā’ti? "
msgstr "‘But reverends, what is that non-physical reincarnation?’ We’d answer like this, "

msgctxt "dn9:45.3"
msgid "Tesaṃ mayaṃ evaṃ puṭṭhā evaṃ byākareyyāma: "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "dn9:45.4"
msgid "‘ayaṃ vā so, āvuso, arūpo attapaṭilābho yassa mayaṃ pahānāya dhammaṃ desema, yathāpaṭipannānaṃ vo saṅkilesikā dhammā pahīyissanti, vodāniyā dhammā abhivaḍḍhissanti, paññāpāripūriṃ vepullattañca diṭṭheva dhamme sayaṃ abhiññā sacchikatvā upasampajja viharissathā’ti. "
msgstr "‘This is that non-physical reincarnation.’ "

# NOTE: This whole argument is odd, and I suspect it is corrupt.
#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc68
msgctxt "dn9:45.5"
msgid "Taṃ kiṃ maññasi, poṭṭhapāda, "
msgstr "What do you think, Poṭṭhapāda? "

msgctxt "dn9:45.6"
msgid "nanu evaṃ sante sappāṭihīrakataṃ bhāsitaṃ sampajjatī”ti? "
msgstr "This being so, doesn’t that statement turn out to have a demonstrable basis?” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "dn9:45.7"
msgid "“Addhā kho, bhante, evaṃ sante sappāṭihīrakataṃ bhāsitaṃ sampajjatī”ti. "
msgstr "“Clearly that’s the case, sir.” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts-cs46, sc69
msgctxt "dn9:46.1"
msgid "“Seyyathāpi, poṭṭhapāda, puriso nisseṇiṃ kareyya pāsādassa ārohaṇāya tasseva pāsādassa heṭṭhā. "
msgstr "“Suppose a man were to build a ladder for climbing up to a stilt longhouse right underneath that longhouse. "

msgctxt "dn9:46.2"
msgid "Tamenaṃ evaṃ vadeyyuṃ: "
msgstr "They’d say to him, "

msgctxt "dn9:46.3"
msgid "‘ambho purisa, yassa tvaṃ pāsādassa ārohaṇāya nisseṇiṃ karosi, jānāsi taṃ pāsādaṃ, puratthimāya vā disāya dakkhiṇāya vā disāya pacchimāya vā disāya uttarāya vā disāya ucco vā nīco vā majjhimo vā’ti? "
msgstr "‘Mister, that stilt longhouse that you’re building a ladder for—do you know whether it’s to the north, south, east, or west? Or whether it’s tall or short or medium?’ "

msgctxt "dn9:46.4"
msgid "So evaṃ vadeyya: "
msgstr "He’d say, "

msgctxt "dn9:46.5"
msgid "‘ayaṃ vā so, āvuso, pāsādo, yassāhaṃ ārohaṇāya nisseṇiṃ karomi, tasseva pāsādassa heṭṭhā’ti. "
msgstr "‘This is that stilt longhouse for which I’m building a ladder, right underneath it.’ "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc70
msgctxt "dn9:46.6"
msgid "Taṃ kiṃ maññasi, poṭṭhapāda, "
msgstr "What do you think, Poṭṭhapāda? "

msgctxt "dn9:46.7"
msgid "nanu evaṃ sante tassa purisassa sappāṭihīrakataṃ bhāsitaṃ sampajjatī”ti? "
msgstr "This being so, doesn’t that man’s statement turn out to have a demonstrable basis?” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "dn9:46.8"
msgid "“Addhā kho, bhante, evaṃ sante tassa purisassa sappāṭihīrakataṃ bhāsitaṃ sampajjatī”ti. "
msgstr "“Clearly that’s the case, sir.” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts-cs47, pts-vp-pli1.199, sc71
msgctxt "dn9:47.1"
msgid "“Evameva kho, poṭṭhapāda, pare ce amhe evaṃ puccheyyuṃ: "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "dn9:47.2"
msgid "‘katamo pana so, āvuso, oḷāriko attapaṭilābho … pe … "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "dn9:47.3"
msgid "katamo pana so, āvuso, manomayo attapaṭilābho … pe … "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "dn9:47.4"
msgid "katamo pana so, āvuso, arūpo attapaṭilābho, yassa tumhe pahānāya dhammaṃ desetha, yathāpaṭipannānaṃ vo saṅkilesikā dhammā pahīyissanti, vodāniyā dhammā abhivaḍḍhissanti, paññāpāripūriṃ vepullattañca diṭṭheva dhamme sayaṃ abhiññā sacchikatvā upasampajja viharissathā’ti? "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "dn9:47.5"
msgid "Tesaṃ mayaṃ evaṃ puṭṭhā evaṃ byākareyyāma: "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "dn9:47.6"
msgid "‘ayaṃ vā so, āvuso, arūpo attapaṭilābho, yassa mayaṃ pahānāya dhammaṃ desema, yathāpaṭipannānaṃ vo saṅkilesikā dhammā pahīyissanti, vodāniyā dhammā abhivaḍḍhissanti, paññāpāripūriṃ vepullattañca diṭṭheva dhamme sayaṃ abhiññā sacchikatvā upasampajja viharissathā’ti. "
msgstr " "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc72
msgctxt "dn9:47.7"
msgid "Taṃ kiṃ maññasi, poṭṭhapāda, nanu evaṃ sante sappāṭihīrakataṃ bhāsitaṃ sampajjatī”ti? "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "dn9:47.8"
msgid "“Addhā kho, bhante, evaṃ sante sappāṭihīrakataṃ bhāsitaṃ sampajjatī”ti. "
msgstr " "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts-cs48, sc73
msgctxt "dn9:48.1"
msgid "Evaṃ vutte, citto hatthisāriputto bhagavantaṃ etadavoca: "
msgstr "When the Buddha had spoken, Citta Hatthisāriputta said, "

msgctxt "dn9:48.2"
msgid "“yasmiṃ, bhante, samaye oḷāriko attapaṭilābho hoti, moghassa tasmiṃ samaye manomayo attapaṭilābho hoti, mogho arūpo attapaṭilābho hoti; "
msgstr "“Sir, while in a substantial reincarnation, are the mind-made and non-physical reincarnations fictitious, "

msgctxt "dn9:48.3"
msgid "oḷāriko vāssa attapaṭilābho tasmiṃ samaye sacco hoti. "
msgstr "and only the substantial reincarnation real? "

msgctxt "dn9:48.4"
msgid "Yasmiṃ, bhante, samaye manomayo attapaṭilābho hoti, moghassa tasmiṃ samaye oḷāriko attapaṭilābho hoti, mogho arūpo attapaṭilābho hoti; "
msgstr "While in a mind-made reincarnation, are the substantial and non-physical reincarnations fictitious, "

msgctxt "dn9:48.5"
msgid "manomayo vāssa attapaṭilābho tasmiṃ samaye sacco hoti. "
msgstr "and only the mind-made reincarnation real? "

msgctxt "dn9:48.6"
msgid "Yasmiṃ, bhante, samaye arūpo attapaṭilābho hoti, moghassa tasmiṃ samaye oḷāriko attapaṭilābho hoti, mogho manomayo attapaṭilābho hoti; "
msgstr "While in a non-physical reincarnation, are the substantial and mind-made reincarnations fictitious, "

msgctxt "dn9:48.7"
msgid "arūpo vāssa attapaṭilābho tasmiṃ samaye sacco hotī”ti. "
msgstr "and only the non-physical reincarnation real?” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts-cs49, pts-vp-pli1.200, sc74
msgctxt "dn9:49.1"
msgid "“Yasmiṃ, citta, samaye oḷāriko attapaṭilābho hoti, neva tasmiṃ samaye manomayo attapaṭilābhoti saṅkhaṃ gacchati, na arūpo attapaṭilābhoti saṅkhaṃ gacchati; "
msgstr "“While in a substantial reincarnation, it’s not referred to as a mind-made or non-physical reincarnation, "

msgctxt "dn9:49.2"
msgid "oḷāriko attapaṭilābhotveva tasmiṃ samaye saṅkhaṃ gacchati. "
msgstr "only as a substantial reincarnation. "

msgctxt "dn9:49.3"
msgid "Yasmiṃ, citta, samaye manomayo attapaṭilābho hoti, neva tasmiṃ samaye oḷāriko attapaṭilābhoti saṅkhaṃ gacchati, na arūpo attapaṭilābhoti saṅkhaṃ gacchati; "
msgstr "While in a mind-made reincarnation, it’s not referred to as a substantial or non-physical reincarnation, "

msgctxt "dn9:49.4"
msgid "manomayo attapaṭilābhotveva tasmiṃ samaye saṅkhaṃ gacchati. "
msgstr "only as a mind-made reincarnation. "

msgctxt "dn9:49.5"
msgid "Yasmiṃ, citta, samaye arūpo attapaṭilābho hoti, neva tasmiṃ samaye oḷāriko attapaṭilābhoti saṅkhaṃ gacchati, na manomayo attapaṭilābhoti saṅkhaṃ gacchati; "
msgstr "While in a non-physical reincarnation, it’s not referred to as a substantial or mind-made reincarnation, "

msgctxt "dn9:49.6"
msgid "arūpo attapaṭilābhotveva tasmiṃ samaye saṅkhaṃ gacchati. "
msgstr "only as a non-physical reincarnation. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc75
msgctxt "dn9:49.7"
msgid "Sace taṃ, citta, evaṃ puccheyyuṃ: "
msgstr "Citta, suppose they were to ask you, "

msgctxt "dn9:49.8"
msgid "‘ahosi tvaṃ atītamaddhānaṃ, na tvaṃ nāhosi; "
msgstr "‘Did you exist in the past? "

msgctxt "dn9:49.9"
msgid "bhavissasi tvaṃ anāgatamaddhānaṃ, na tvaṃ na bhavissasi; "
msgstr "Will you exist in the future? "

msgctxt "dn9:49.10"
msgid "atthi tvaṃ etarahi, na tvaṃ natthī’ti. "
msgstr "Do you exist now?’ "

msgctxt "dn9:49.11"
msgid "Evaṃ puṭṭho tvaṃ, citta, kinti byākareyyāsī”ti? "
msgstr "How would you answer?” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc76
msgctxt "dn9:49.12"
msgid "“Sace maṃ, bhante, evaṃ puccheyyuṃ: "
msgstr "“Sir, if they were to ask me this, "

msgctxt "dn9:49.13"
msgid "‘ahosi tvaṃ atītamaddhānaṃ, na tvaṃ na ahosi; "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "dn9:49.14"
msgid "bhavissasi tvaṃ anāgatamaddhānaṃ, na tvaṃ na bhavissasi; "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "dn9:49.15"
msgid "atthi tvaṃ etarahi, na tvaṃ natthī’ti. "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "dn9:49.16"
msgid "Evaṃ puṭṭho ahaṃ, bhante, evaṃ byākareyyaṃ: "
msgstr "I’d answer like this, "

msgctxt "dn9:49.17"
msgid "‘ahosāhaṃ atītamaddhānaṃ, nāhaṃ na ahosiṃ; "
msgstr "‘I existed in the past. "

msgctxt "dn9:49.18"
msgid "bhavissāmahaṃ anāgatamaddhānaṃ, nāhaṃ na bhavissāmi; "
msgstr "I will exist in the future. "

msgctxt "dn9:49.19"
msgid "atthāhaṃ etarahi, nāhaṃ natthī’ti. "
msgstr "I exist now.’ "

msgctxt "dn9:49.20"
msgid "Evaṃ puṭṭho ahaṃ, bhante, evaṃ byākareyyan”ti. "
msgstr "That’s how I’d answer.” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts-cs50, sc77
msgctxt "dn9:50.1"
msgid "“Sace pana taṃ, citta, evaṃ puccheyyuṃ: "
msgstr "“But Citta, suppose they were to ask you, "

#. VAR: sova → svera (bj, pts1) | soyeva (s1-3) | so ca (mr)
msgctxt "dn9:50.2"
msgid "‘yo te ahosi atīto attapaṭilābho, sova te attapaṭilābho sacco, mogho anāgato, mogho paccuppanno? "
msgstr "‘Is the reincarnation you had in the past your only real one, and those of the future and present fictitious? "

#. VAR: Yo → yo va (pts1)
msgctxt "dn9:50.3"
msgid "Yo te bhavissati anāgato attapaṭilābho, sova te attapaṭilābho sacco, mogho atīto, mogho paccuppanno? "
msgstr "Is the reincarnation you will have in the future your only real one, and those of the past and present fictitious? "

msgctxt "dn9:50.4"
msgid "Yo te etarahi paccuppanno attapaṭilābho, sova te attapaṭilābho sacco, mogho atīto, mogho anāgato’ti. "
msgstr "Is the reincarnation you have now your only real one, and those of the past and future fictitious?’ "

msgctxt "dn9:50.5"
msgid "Evaṃ puṭṭho tvaṃ, citta, kinti byākareyyāsī”ti? "
msgstr "How would you answer?” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts-vp-pli1.201, sc78
msgctxt "dn9:50.6"
msgid "“Sace pana maṃ, bhante, evaṃ puccheyyuṃ: "
msgstr "“Sir, if they were to ask me this, "

msgctxt "dn9:50.7"
msgid "‘yo te ahosi atīto attapaṭilābho, sova te attapaṭilābho sacco, mogho anāgato, mogho paccuppanno. "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "dn9:50.8"
msgid "Yo te bhavissati anāgato attapaṭilābho, sova te attapaṭilābho sacco, mogho atīto, mogho paccuppanno. "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "dn9:50.9"
msgid "Yo te etarahi paccuppanno attapaṭilābho, sova te attapaṭilābho sacco, mogho atīto, mogho anāgato’ti. "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "dn9:50.10"
msgid "Evaṃ puṭṭho ahaṃ, bhante, evaṃ byākareyyaṃ: "
msgstr "I’d answer like this, "

msgctxt "dn9:50.11"
msgid "‘yo me ahosi atīto attapaṭilābho, sova me attapaṭilābho tasmiṃ samaye sacco ahosi, mogho anāgato, mogho paccuppanno. "
msgstr "‘The reincarnation I had in the past was real at that time, and those of the future and present fictitious. "

msgctxt "dn9:50.12"
msgid "Yo me bhavissati anāgato attapaṭilābho, sova me attapaṭilābho tasmiṃ samaye sacco bhavissati, mogho atīto, mogho paccuppanno. "
msgstr "The reincarnation I will have in the future will be real at the time, and those of the past and present fictitious. "

msgctxt "dn9:50.13"
msgid "Yo me etarahi paccuppanno attapaṭilābho, sova me attapaṭilābho sacco, mogho atīto, mogho anāgato’ti. "
msgstr "The reincarnation I have now is real at this time, and those of the past and future fictitious.’ "

msgctxt "dn9:50.14"
msgid "Evaṃ puṭṭho ahaṃ, bhante, evaṃ byākareyyan”ti. "
msgstr "That’s how I’d answer.” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts-cs51, sc79
msgctxt "dn9:51.1"
msgid "“Evameva kho, citta, yasmiṃ samaye oḷāriko attapaṭilābho hoti, neva tasmiṃ samaye manomayo attapaṭilābhoti saṅkhaṃ gacchati, na arūpo attapaṭilābhoti saṅkhaṃ gacchati. "
msgstr "“In the same way, while in any one of the three reincarnations, it’s not referred to as the other two, only under its own name. "

msgctxt "dn9:51.2"
msgid "Oḷāriko attapaṭilābhotveva tasmiṃ samaye saṅkhaṃ gacchati. "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "dn9:51.3"
msgid "Yasmiṃ, citta, samaye manomayo attapaṭilābho hoti … pe … "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "dn9:51.4"
msgid "yasmiṃ, citta, samaye arūpo attapaṭilābho hoti, neva tasmiṃ samaye oḷāriko attapaṭilābhoti saṅkhaṃ gacchati, na manomayo attapaṭilābhoti saṅkhaṃ gacchati; "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "dn9:51.5"
msgid "arūpo attapaṭilābhotveva tasmiṃ samaye saṅkhaṃ gacchati. "
msgstr " "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts-cs52, pts-vp-pli1.202, sc80
msgctxt "dn9:52.1"
msgid "Seyyathāpi, citta, gavā khīraṃ, khīramhā dadhi, dadhimhā navanītaṃ, navanītamhā sappi, sappimhā sappimaṇḍo. "
msgstr "From a cow comes milk, from milk comes curds, from curds come butter, from butter comes ghee, and from ghee comes cream of ghee. And the cream of ghee is said to be the best of these. "

msgctxt "dn9:52.2"
msgid "Yasmiṃ samaye khīraṃ hoti, neva tasmiṃ samaye dadhīti saṅkhaṃ gacchati, na navanītanti saṅkhaṃ gacchati, na sappīti saṅkhaṃ gacchati, na sappimaṇḍoti saṅkhaṃ gacchati; "
msgstr "While it’s milk, it’s not referred to as curds, butter, ghee, or cream of ghee. "

msgctxt "dn9:52.3"
msgid "khīrantveva tasmiṃ samaye saṅkhaṃ gacchati. "
msgstr "It’s only referred to as milk. "

msgctxt "dn9:52.4"
msgid "Yasmiṃ samaye dadhi hoti … pe … "
msgstr "While it’s curd "

msgctxt "dn9:52.5"
msgid "navanītaṃ hoti … "
msgstr "or butter "

msgctxt "dn9:52.6"
msgid "sappi hoti … "
msgstr "or ghee "

msgctxt "dn9:52.7"
msgid "sappimaṇḍo hoti, neva tasmiṃ samaye khīranti saṅkhaṃ gacchati, na dadhīti saṅkhaṃ gacchati, na navanītanti saṅkhaṃ gacchati, na sappīti saṅkhaṃ gacchati; "
msgstr "or cream of ghee, it’s not referred to as anything else, "

msgctxt "dn9:52.8"
msgid "sappimaṇḍotveva tasmiṃ samaye saṅkhaṃ gacchati. "
msgstr "only under its own name. "

#. REF: pts-cs53
msgctxt "dn9:53.1"
msgid "Evameva kho, citta, yasmiṃ samaye oḷāriko attapaṭilābho hoti … pe … "
msgstr "In the same way, while in any one of the three reincarnations, it’s not referred to as the other two, only under its own name. "

msgctxt "dn9:53.2"
msgid "yasmiṃ, citta, samaye manomayo attapaṭilābho hoti … pe … "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "dn9:53.3"
msgid "yasmiṃ, citta, samaye arūpo attapaṭilābho hoti, neva tasmiṃ samaye oḷāriko attapaṭilābhoti saṅkhaṃ gacchati, na manomayo attapaṭilābhoti saṅkhaṃ gacchati; "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "dn9:53.4"
msgid "arūpo attapaṭilābhotveva tasmiṃ samaye saṅkhaṃ gacchati. "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "dn9:53.5"
msgid "Imā kho, citta, lokasamaññā lokaniruttiyo lokavohārā lokapaññattiyo, yāhi tathāgato voharati aparāmasan”ti. "
msgstr "These are the world’s usages, terms, expressions, and descriptions, which the Realized One uses without misapprehending them.” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts-cs54, sc81
msgctxt "dn9:54.1"
msgid "Evaṃ vutte, poṭṭhapādo paribbājako bhagavantaṃ etadavoca: "
msgstr "When he had spoken, the wanderer Poṭṭhapāda said to the Buddha, "

msgctxt "dn9:54.2"
msgid "“abhikkantaṃ, bhante, abhikkantaṃ, bhante. "
msgstr "“Excellent, sir! Excellent! "

msgctxt "dn9:54.3"
msgid "Seyyathāpi, bhante, nikkujjitaṃ vā ukkujjeyya, paṭicchannaṃ vā vivareyya, mūḷhassa vā maggaṃ ācikkheyya, andhakāre vā telapajjotaṃ dhāreyya: ‘cakkhumanto rūpāni dakkhantī’ti; evamevaṃ bhagavatā anekapariyāyena dhammo pakāsito. "
msgstr "As if he were righting the overturned, or revealing the hidden, or pointing out the path to the lost, or lighting a lamp in the dark so people with good eyes can see what’s there, so too the Buddha has made the teaching clear in many ways. "

msgctxt "dn9:54.4"
msgid "Esāhaṃ, bhante, bhagavantaṃ saraṇaṃ gacchāmi dhammañca bhikkhusaṅghañca. "
msgstr "I go for refuge to the Buddha, to the teaching, and to the mendicant Saṅgha. "

msgctxt "dn9:54.5"
msgid "Upāsakaṃ maṃ bhagavā dhāretu ajjatagge pāṇupetaṃ saraṇaṃ gatan”ti. "
msgstr "From this day forth, may the Buddha remember me as a lay follower who has gone for refuge for life.” "

#. HTML: </p><h3>
msgctxt "dn9:54.6"
msgid "2.3. Cittahatthisāriputtaupasampadā "
msgstr "2.3. The Ordination of Citta Hatthisāriputta "

#. HTML: </h3><p>
#. REF: pts-cs55, sc82
msgctxt "dn9:55.1"
msgid "Citto pana hatthisāriputto bhagavantaṃ etadavoca: "
msgstr "But Citta Hatthisāriputta said to the Buddha, "

msgctxt "dn9:55.2"
msgid "“abhikkantaṃ, bhante, abhikkantaṃ, bhante. "
msgstr "“Excellent, sir! Excellent! "

msgctxt "dn9:55.3"
msgid "Seyyathāpi, bhante, nikkujjitaṃ vā ukkujjeyya, paṭicchannaṃ vā vivareyya, mūḷhassa vā maggaṃ ācikkheyya, andhakāre vā telapajjotaṃ dhāreyya: ‘cakkhumanto rūpāni dakkhantī’ti; evamevaṃ bhagavatā anekapariyāyena dhammo pakāsito. "
msgstr "As if he were righting the overturned, or revealing the hidden, or pointing out the path to the lost, or lighting a lamp in the dark so people with good eyes can see what’s there, so too the Buddha has made the teaching clear in many ways. "

msgctxt "dn9:55.4"
msgid "Esāhaṃ, bhante, bhagavantaṃ saraṇaṃ gacchāmi dhammañca bhikkhusaṅghañca. "
msgstr "I go for refuge to the Buddha, to the teaching, and to the mendicant Saṅgha. "

msgctxt "dn9:55.5"
msgid "Labheyyāhaṃ, bhante, bhagavato santike pabbajjaṃ, labheyyaṃ upasampadan”ti. "
msgstr "Sir, may I receive the going forth, the ordination in the Buddha’s presence?” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts-cs56, pts-vp-pli1.203, sc83
msgctxt "dn9:56.1"
msgid "Alattha kho citto hatthisāriputto bhagavato santike pabbajjaṃ, alattha upasampadaṃ. "
msgstr "And Citta Hatthisāriputta received the going forth, the ordination in the Buddha’s presence. "

msgctxt "dn9:56.2"
msgid "Acirūpasampanno kho panāyasmā citto hatthisāriputto eko vūpakaṭṭho appamatto ātāpī pahitatto viharanto na cirasseva—yassatthāya kulaputtā sammadeva agārasmā anagāriyaṃ pabbajanti, tadanuttaraṃ—brahmacariyapariyosānaṃ diṭṭheva dhamme sayaṃ abhiññā sacchikatvā upasampajja vihāsi. "
msgstr "Not long after his ordination, Venerable Citta Hatthisāriputta, living alone, withdrawn, diligent, keen, and resolute, soon realized the supreme end of the spiritual path in this very life. He lived having achieved with his own insight the goal for which gentlemen rightly go forth from the lay life to homelessness. "

msgctxt "dn9:56.3"
msgid "“khīṇā jāti, vusitaṃ brahmacariyaṃ, kataṃ karaṇīyaṃ, nāparaṃ itthAttāyā”ti abbhaññāsi. "
msgstr "He understood: “Rebirth is ended; the spiritual journey has been completed; what had to be done has been done; there is no return to any state of existence.” "

# NOTE: Not without some wavering, according to AN 6.60
msgctxt "dn9:56.4"
msgid "Aññataro kho panāyasmā citto hatthisāriputto arahataṃ ahosīti. "
msgstr "And Venerable Citta Hatthisāriputta became one of the perfected. "

#. HTML: </p><p class="endsutta">
msgctxt "dn9:56.5"
msgid "Poṭṭhapādasuttaṃ niṭṭhitaṃ navamaṃ. "
msgstr ""

